                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-353" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 353 History of Montreal (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27542" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : The history of Montreal from its beginnings to the present day. Montreal's economic, social, cultural and political role within the French and British empires, North America, Canada, and Quebec; the city's  linguistic and ethnic diversity.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              This course is not scheduled for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

